{
  "texts": [
    "However, these values often vary across different magnitudes, ranging from 1 to more than 10 million in some cases.",
    "For example, the distribution of target values in the YouTube live streaming data set is illustrated in Fig. 4.",
    "Predicting target values across such a large and imbalanced distribution of magnitudes poses a challenge for the proposed model, potentially resulting in significant biases in the prediction results.To address this challenge, we implement a transformation on the prediction target values, converting them into percentages of changes.",
    "Thus, the proposed model predicts the percentage of change in the popularity degree values rather than the original values.",
    "As depicted in Fig 5, the percentages only range from -1 to 2 after eliminating outliers."
  ]
}